{"type":"message","id":"26f53374","parentId":"4a29ca13","timestamp":"2026-04-24T16:48:10.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The extension is a Manifest V3 Chrome extension. Firefox can load it as a temporary extension. Let me check if Firefox is available and how to load it.\n\nActually, the user is on Linux (Ubuntu/WSL). Let me check if Firefox is installed and how to load the extension.\n\nFor Firefox, you can load a temporary extension by going to `about:debugging` and clicking \"This Firefox\" > \"Load Temporary Add-on\" and selecting the manifest.json file.\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to do this programmatically.\n\nActually, let me just tell the user how to load it manually since it's a one-time thing. Or I can try to use Firefox's remote debugging API.\n\n\nSince Firefox on Linux doesn't support the `about:debugging` API that Chrome does, I'll need to guide the user through the manual steps to load the extension.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n扩展 build 好了，在 `dist/` 目录下。Firefox 加载临时扩展的方式：\n\n1. 打开 Firefox，地址栏输入 **`about:debugging`** 回车\n2. 点左侧 **\"This Firefox\"**（本Firefox）\n3. 点 **\"临时加载附加组件\"** 按钮\n4. 找到 `/home/kensoulstar/OpenCLI-main/extension/manifest.json`，选中打开\n\n或者我试试能不能通过 Firefox CLI 自动加载：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"380022437","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which firefox 2>/dev/null; firefox --version 2>/dev/null; which firefox-esr 2>/dev/null; firefox-esr --version 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lm_studio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777049274163,"responseId":"chatcmpl-gur6u9kmyfuc072bhhkw"}}
