{"type":"message","id":"3dd2a848","parentId":"13a7c9c8","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:16:21.069Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error says \"Browser Bridge extension not connected\" and mentions Chrome/Chromium. The OpenCLI extension is designed to work with Chrome's CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol), not Firefox. Firefox doesn't support the same debugging protocol that Chrome extensions use for CDP connections.\n\nThe key issue is that OpenCLI's extension uses Chrome's `debugger` permission and CDP to communicate with the daemon. Firefox doesn't support this. The user would need to use Chrome/Chromium for the extension to work.\n\nLet me check the OpenCLI docs to confirm this.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOpenCLI 的扩展依赖 **Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP)**，这是 Chrome/Chromium 专有的协议，Firefox 不支持。所以扩展装到 Firefox 上虽然能加载，但无法建立连接。\n\n有两个方案：\n\n1. **装个 Chromium** — 最简单，`sudo apt install chromium-browser` 或者 `sudo snap install chromium`，然后把扩展装到 Chromium 里\n2. **用 Chrome** — 如果系统有 Chrome 的话\n\n要我帮你装 Chromium？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lm_studio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777050970063,"responseId":"chatcmpl-q0pl23shoghyxrrarqqxu"}}
