{"type":"message","id":"47697281","parentId":"c78a21ec","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:25:41.958Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System (untrusted): [2026-04-25 01:24:42 GMT+8] Exec failed (kind-gul, signal SIGTERM) :: code: BROWSER_CONNECT message: Browser Bridge extension not connected help: |- Make sure Chrome/Chromium is open and the extension is enabled. If the extension is installed, try: …\n\nAn async command you ran earlier has completed. The result is shown in the system messages above. Handle the result internally. Do not relay it to the user unless explicitly requested.\nCurrent time: Saturday, April 25th, 2026 - 01:25 (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-04-24 17:25 UTC"}],"timestamp":1777051541952}}
{"type":"message","id":"2896b47e","parentId":"47697281","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:26:17.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user installed the extension in Chromium but it's still not connecting. The issue is likely the Chromium snap sandbox preventing the extension from communicating with the local daemon on port 19825. Let me check the extension details and try to fix the snap permissions.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n让我检查一下扩展连接情况和 snap 权限：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"837465776","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 chromium snap 的权限\nsnap connections chromium | grep -E '19825|network' 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; snap info chromium 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; ls /home/kensoulstar/snap/chromium/common/.config/opencli* 2>/dev/null || echo \"no opencli config dir\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lm_studio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777051541964,"responseId":"chatcmpl-mg0w1fbw3rg15ysjvxvo"}}
