{"type":"message","id":"4909cb01","parentId":"e0c55bd0","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:28:14.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The daemon is hardcoded to listen on 127.0.0.1:19825. The issue is that the Chromium snap extension can't connect to localhost due to sandbox restrictions.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to fix this by:\n1. Making the daemon listen on all interfaces (0.0.0.0)\n2. Or suggesting the user install Chrome instead of Chromium snap\n3. Or checking if there's a snap permission that needs to be adjusted\n\nActually, the snap sandbox issue is a known problem. The extension runs in the Chromium sandbox and can't reach localhost directly. Let me check if there's a way to fix this by adjusting the snap permissions or if we need to suggest installing Chrome.\n\nLet me try to check if the extension is properly loaded and if there's a way to make it work.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n问题找到了。Chromium snap 版有沙箱限制，扩展无法连接到 localhost:19825。\n\n有两个解决方案：\n\n**方案 1：给 Chromium snap 加网络权限**（试试这个）\n```bash\nsudo snap connect chromium:network-bind\n```\n\n**方案 2：安装 Chrome**（更可靠）\n```bash\nwget -q -O - https://dl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/google-chrome.gpg\necho \"deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/google-chrome.gpg] http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/ stable main\" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/google-chrome.list\nsudo apt update && sudo apt install -y google-chrome-stable\n```\n\n你选哪个？方案 1 快但可能不管用，方案 2 更稳。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lm_studio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777051676645,"responseId":"chatcmpl-qxepap9a8xr9681sjzlw9"}}
