{"type":"message","id":"47153573","parentId":"d5fb7005","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:33:48.776Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The snap connections look fine - network-bind is connected. The issue might be that the extension needs to be reloaded in Chromium after the manifest change. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe extension connects to the daemon via WebSocket. The daemon listens on 127.0.0.1:19825. The extension should be able to connect to localhost from within the Chromium snap.\n\nActually, the real issue might be that the Chromium snap doesn't have the right permissions, or the extension needs to be reloaded. Let me check if there's a way to debug the extension's connection attempt.\n\n\nThe snap connections show network-bind is connected, so that's not the issue. The extension manifest has been updated and reloaded in Chromium, but it's still not connecting. I should verify the extension is properly enabled and check the Chromium developer console for any errors.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nsnap 的网络权限看起来没问题。问题可能是 Chromium 里扩展需要重新加载。\n\n你在 Chromium 里：\n\n1. 打开 `chrome://extensions`\n2. 找到 **OpenCLI** 扩展\n3. 点**详细信息**，确认状态是 **\"已启用\"**\n4. 点扩展的 **选项** 页面，看看有没有连接地址的配置\n5. 如果看到错误提示，告诉我是什么\n\n另外，在 Chromium 地址栏输入 `chrome://extensions` 后，点 OpenCLI 扩展的 **检查背景页** 链接，看看控制台有没有报错。\n\n或者你直接告诉我，要不要我装个 Chrome？Chrome 没有 snap 沙箱问题，更稳。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"lm_studio","model":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777052012320,"responseId":"chatcmpl-c69q62xduzmg34e69jkoz"}}
